The article announces the launch of a new COVID-19 vaccine, which will be administered once a year in the fall. The vaccine is designed to provide strong protection against the new Omicron strain of the virus and can be obtained by individuals aged 12 and older at various locations such as pharmacies and health centers. Similar to the annual flu shot, this vaccine will be updated annually to target the dominant variant of the virus. The article emphasizes the importance of getting vaccinated to reduce the risk of contracting and spreading COVID-19, as well as the risk of severe illness. It concludes by encouraging individuals to find a vaccination location near their home or work and get vaccinated before winter arrives.